12/04/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The senior ruling Democratic Liberal Party (PDL) will hold its next congress this summer on July 16th, the party's National Co-ordination Council decided at a meeting Friday (April 9th). Members of the council also adopted a new measure introducing a majority vote to determine senior positions. Members with the highest number of votes will start filling positions from the top down, in contrast to the current practice. (Cotidianul, Antena 3, Realitatea, Evenimentul Zilei, Ziare - 09/04/10)
